It is rude to compare the taste of cum to the traditional food of another country.
In the first place, kimchi was not popular enough to regard it as an idiomatic expression in Western countries.
Also, when someone else hears a joke, it's no longer a joke if you misunderstand or feel bad.
Didn't you learn in school ethics class?
And Netflix Korea channel deleted the story of Kimchi from the trailer
If it weren't for real racism, it wouldn't have been deleted from the Korean channel.
Netflix knew it was racist, but it was responsible for not deleting it.
Please delete that scene immediately and explain it.

Do not ask people in non-English speaking countries to speak English.
Don't you have a translator? Don't you know how to use it at all?

남의 나라 전통 음식으로 정액 맛에 비유하는 건 무례한 언행입니다.
애초에 김치가 서구권 국가에서 저것을 관용적으로 쓰일 수 있는 표현이라 여길 만큼 대중적으로 보급되지 않았습니다.
또한 다른 사람이 농담을 들었을 때, 오해하거나 기분이 나빠지만 그것은 더 이상 농담이 아닙니다.
그리고 넷플릭스 한국 채널에서는 예고편 속 김치 이야기를 삭제했습니다.
이게 진짜 인종차별이 아니었다면, 한국 채널에서 삭제되지 않았을 겁니다.
넷플릭스는 저 말이 인종차별적 내용이라는 걸 알고 있었으나, 삭제하지 않은 것에 대해 책임이 있습니다.
넷플릭스는 즉시 저 장면을 삭제하고, 해명해 주시기 바랍니다.

비영어권 국가의 사람들에게 영어로 말해달라고 하지 마십시오. 당신네들은 번역기가 없나요?
아예 사용할 줄도 모르나요?

snippet.textDisplay:
To all people who think the line "my cum tastes like Kimchi" is not problematic:

1. If you are not from that country or grew up with the culture (which is Korea), it's important to listen to Korean peoples' voices before concluding yourself saying "it's just a joke, take it easy."

2. Kimchi is not just a food here in this context. A young white British boy going to a nice British school saying in an unexpected, almost disgusted tone about his cum tasting like Kimchi means disrespect to the food and the culture that proudly embraces and shares it.

In saying the remarks you become so much worse then the “made in bad taste Kimchi joke”. It makes me sad to see that this is what you turn to.
Additionally do NOT make any racist jokes about color or eye shape even to quip a previously racist joke about Naziism. I cannot believe I need to explain this. Everyone who says things like this IS the problem. Please stop. Try respecting each other for once . It can take you very far and is the only way to you can create change. PLEASE RESPECT EACH-OTHER.

snippet.textDisplay:
Dear Koreans,


I live in Korea and I understand that joking about sexual things is not normal. But in UK, US, Canada, it is normal to joke about sexual things. I don't think the writers of the show meant it as an insult. Kimchi has a strong, sour smell to westerners because we did not grow up with it. I smell it everywhere in Korea, even in schools. I am sure most Koreans no longer notice because it is normal to them. I think it is a joke about its unique smell/taste is sour, and not meant to be an insult. The show is very good, you should watch it.

snippet.textDisplay: Imagine getting outraged saying kimchi is being compared to semen and that the joke is racist. Kimchi is a well known food to younger generations, and with its sour, spicy taste, it would be quite concerning for someone's semen to taste like that, and the unusual and unexpected nature of that is what makes the joke more impactful. No racism, no offense to kimchi, no comparing the taste of kimchi to semen. What's worse is seeing both sides succumb to making horrifically racist comments because of a joke that isn't even racist.
